    "Three different systems for analyzing peer comments were used by Huang et al. (2023), classifying peer comments in terms of cognitive content and affective state.",
    "The Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) model had the best results and improved feedback with significantly reduced student burnout.",
    "Individuals who received more suggestive feedback experienced a greater reduction in emotional exhaustion.",
    "By contrast, when receiving more negative feedback and/or reinforcement without guidance, learners tended to have a worse emotional experience and demonstrated poorer self-learning behavior.",
    "Eight papers focused on review helpfulness and problem detection."
